<biogHist>
<abstract>Ruhamah, run by the Baptist Homes Trust, was a children's home established in May 1959 at South Hurstville for boys over the age of seven. Younger boys and girls were housed at Karingal Children's Home. Ruhamah was officially opened on 15 August 1959. In November 1975 the home was relocated to Oatley. Ruhamah remained a home for boys until 1980 when it was changed to a home for girls aged from fifteen to eighteen years. Ruhamah closed in 1985.</abstract>
